### Licence Text

**CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal**

**CERN**

**Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal**

**Preamble**

Community knowledge, like technological knowledge, is a strategic resource for the economy. Open sharing of this knowledge allows everyone to contribute to building a community of practitioners. This community of practice is both a source of innovation and a guarantee of reproducibility and reliability.

CERN has more than sixty years of experience in sharing technological knowledge and considers this approach the best way to create a collaborative community to support its mission to share knowledge through open access publishing, software licensing schemes such as the GNU GPL, and now hardware designs.

The GNU GPL was created by the Free Software Foundation. It is designed to ensure that software is shared freely and openly, and remains that way, by requiring that any derivatives of the software be made available under the same terms. This CERN Open Hardware Licence has been created with similar principles in mind.

This CERN Open Hardware Licence aims to promote the sharing of knowledge, by guaranteeing that hardware designs remain free and open for all to use, modify and distribute, as long as the conditions of this licence are met.

To promote the uptake of this Licence, CERN has published the text of the Licence in several languages, including English, French, German and Spanish. In the event of any inconsistency between the English version and a translation, the English version shall prevail.

This Licence is available in two variants: Strongly Reciprocal (S) and Weakly Reciprocal (W). The only difference between the two is the scope of the Reciprocity obligation. This is the Strongly Reciprocal version.

**CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal**

**Version 2.0, 30 August 2021**

**1. Definitions**

1.1 "Accept" means to access, use or Share Licensed Source or any part thereof, or to exercise any Licensed Right in any Licensed Material or part thereof.

1.2 "Active Development" means any work on the Licensed Source, whether publicly available or not, by You, and includes any modifications made to the Licensed Source by You.

1.3 "Application" means a design which incorporates, or which is based on, one or more Licensed Modules.

1.4 "Available Source" means Source from which a particular modification or derivative can be produced.

1.5 "Contribute" means to transfer ownership of modifications to the Licensed Source to the Licensor, as provided in Clause 5.1.

1.6 "Design File" means a file which describes the hardware design, or any part thereof, of the Licensed Material.

1.7 "External Modification" means a modification made to a Licensed Module which is not incorporated into the Available Source for that Licensed Module.

1.8 "Externally Manufactured Product" means a Product which is manufactured by You, or on Your behalf, using a Licensed Module, but where the Licensed Module has not been manufactured by You, or on Your behalf, from the Available Source for that Licensed Module.

1.9 "Licensed Material" means the hardware design made available by the Licensor under this Licence, as indicated by a copyright notice included in or with the Licensed Material.

1.10 "Licensed Module" means a module which is made available under the terms of this Licence.

1.11 "Licensed Product" means any product or device which incorporates, or which is based on, one or more Licensed Modules.

1.12 "Licensed Rights" means the rights to use, reproduce, modify, display, perform, sublicense, and distribute Licensed Material.

1.13 "Licensed Source" means the Source made available under this Licence.

