**4. Reciprocity**

4.1 If You Share any part of the Licensed Material, or any derivative of it, You must do so only under the terms of this Licence.

4.2 If You Manufacture a Licensed Product, You must make the Source of that Licensed Product available under the terms of this Licence.

4.3 If You Manufacture an Externally Manufactured Product, You must:

    a) ensure that the Source for the Licensed Module used in that Externally Manufactured Product is made available under the terms of this Licence; and

    b) notify any recipient of the Externally Manufactured Product that it is subject to the terms of this Licence.

4.4 The Reciprocity obligation in Clause 4.2 extends to the entire Source of the Licensed Product. This means that You must make the Source available for the entire Product, not just for the Licensed Modules that it incorporates. The Source for the Product must be made available under the terms of this Licence.

